Game was OK, but text was really small and a stuggle to read on a phone. This spoiled the game play a little, and half way through the game, I'd had enough and wanted it to end. In fact, I seemed to be wanting it to end for ages, and it just went on and on. I don't usually complain about long games, but in this instance I found I was skipping through the puzzles, particularly the lantern puzzles, just to get to the end of the game. Might have been better on a tablet.

I like most everything about the game - great graphics, good story, new ideas. But, not a 5 because 1) some directions are not as clear as they could be, 2) if I pay for a game, I should NOT have to deal with pop-up ads every time I come back to the game...irritating!!
I love big fish games and this one was no let down I give it a 8 out of 10 it would be a 10 out of 10 if the price were a big lower  keep the great game's coming

This was not a good game in my humble opinion.... The story line was actually interesting but I pretty much skipped every puzzle. I thought the hidden object games were different and I liked that as some can be boring and stale..BUT many objects made no sense or were just plain incorrect.. The ending was torture and just felt like someone turned the lights out ...it just ended!  Just saying!!
Liked the game.  Would have given it 5 stars but can't get the bonus chapter to work it just goes to a black screen.

Beautiful graphics ,Great story good game play , puzzles, hops, I have had no problems or glitches while playing this game.The entire series of myths of world games are my absolute favorite I would recommend them all. But this one by far was my favorite hope there's more to come.

I can't believe I paid full price for this game. I wish I could get a refund. I can't even finish it. The hidden object games are the worst... I've loved all other big fish hidden object games starting with Ravenhearst. This was a disappointment.

So far, I love the game, but none of the souvenirs are showing up. I even started over, but where the guide shows there should be souvenirs, nothing is there. I can find the acorns though.

Would b a fun game but printing so small I had to use the hint button to progress. Mini games and HOGS were just right. Excellent graphics and music. Story line flowed. Would recommend to a friend IF played on TABLET. Not recommended for phone.

Eipix are great at designing HOGs. Artwork is beautifully detailed. The game play is simple, but smooth. Some touch response issues in puzzles, but a good game.

Enjoying the game but loses a star for the repetition of the puzzle using the lantern.  Suppose it's for continuity but gets boring.  Overall tho interesting storyline and quite long gameplay so it is worth a buy.

I hope Big Fish continues to have mini games like these I don't know about everyone else but I get tired of the same old seek and find words to the picture. Way to go big fish another job well done!

Amazingly well done in terms of graphics, length of play, puzzles, and HOPS. Love the travel map, the collectibles that you can revisit in the extra content, bonus game, and the credits were very enjoyable, almost like Monty Python. The story really didn't make sense but nevertheless fun, slightly creepy, and can't wait for another one!

I play for fun not abstract thinking or to brush up on my geometry/math, etc. Also like the games w/a map that shows the morphs, collectibles. More of those would be be nice
